-- 50 senators support Bernanke, 22 opposed
-- 
-- Wed Jan 27, 2010 6:02pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/01/27/us-bernanke-count-idUSTRE60Q6WQ20100127

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The following is the latest result of an ongoing Reuters poll of U.S. senators on whether they will support Ben Bernanke's nomination to a second four-year term as Federal Reserve chairman. 

 YES: 50 (36 Democrats, 13 Republicans, 1 Independent) NO: 22 (6 Democrats, 15 Republicans, 1 Independent) UNDECIDED/UNANNOUNCED: 28 (16 Democrats, 12 Republicans) (Reporting by Reuters Washington bureau)